# demo-builder — AdvertEyes (improve pass 3 / fix run)

## Root Cause Fixed

deploy-test identified ONE blocker: infinite 401 reload loop at login caused by two cooperating bugs:

1. `src/api/index.ts` — 401 interceptor unconditionally redirected to `/demos/adverteyes/` on any 401, including unauthenticated requests made before login.
2. `src/contexts/AlertsContext.tsx` — `fetchBookings()`/`fetchCampaigns()` fired on mount with no auth guard, generating 401s on the login page (triggering the interceptor above -> reload -> repeat).

## Changes Made

### `src/api/index.ts` (2-line fix)
Added `hadToken` check before redirect — now only redirects on session expiry (token existed then 401 = real auth failure), not on unauthenticated API calls made from the login page.

### `src/contexts/AlertsContext.tsx`
- Added `import { useAuth } from './AuthContext'`
- Added `const { user } = useAuth()` in provider
- Changed `useEffect` dependency from `[]` to `[user]` with early `if (!user) return` guard

AlertsContext now waits for an authenticated user before calling any API endpoints, eliminating all unauthenticated 401s at login.

## Build & Deploy

- `npm run build` — success, 954 modules, no errors
- Replaced stale JS bundle: `index-Dr-vqYnr.js` -> `index-VmW0JRvj.js` (git rm old, git add new)
- `index.html` updated to reference new bundle hash
- CSS unchanged (`index-BsSdBTbi.css`)
- Files staged in `michaelwegter.com`, ready for `deploy` step to commit + push

